description: From Latin supervenient-, stem of superveniens, present participle of supervenio (“to come to or in addition to, to overtake”).

adjectives.description: supervenient (comparative more supervenient, superlative most supervenient)

entries.meaning: (logic, philosophy, of a set of properties) In a relationship with another set such that membership in the other set implies membership in the present set
examples: If mental properties are supervenient on physical properties, people with identical bodies will also have identical minds.

entries.meaning: Supervening; occurring subsequently; coming after something, especially when not causally connected.
